                <head>No. 278.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Shishkin</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Evarts</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Russia</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1877-06-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 26, 1877</date>. (Received June
                        26.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: His Majesty the Emperor, my august sovereign,
                    deigned to order on the 29th april,/11th May, last, that any vessel sailing
                    under a neutral flag should have the right, during the entire duration of the
                    present war with Turkey, to engage in the coasting trade between the Russian
                    ports of the Black Sea and the Sea of Azov.</p>
                <p>In bringing this decision to the knowledge of the Federal Government, I avail
                    myself of this occasion to beg you, Mr. Secretary of State, to accept the
                    assurance of my very high consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>N. SHISHKIN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
